From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Fruit Jam Linux <fruitjam-linux@local>
Date: Thu, 18 Jun 2026 00:25:00 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] misc: shrink Fruit Jam usbhost HCD ACK arm gap

Hardware testing of the gated HCD setup path showed a clean timeout waiting
for the hub ACK:

  hcd-control setup-arm-ack tx-len=50
  last-rx-result -110 pid 0x00 len 0

That path was using a 16-byte idle pad between the SETUP token and DATA0 packet
so the CPU could arm RX after the first EOP. The pad is useful, but 16 encoded
idle bytes stretches the host inter-packet delay far enough that the CH334F hub
may discard the setup transaction before the host reaches the DATA0 packet.

Keep the gated ACK strategy, but reduce the arm pad to 4 bytes. This still gives
the Linux MMIO handoff a bounded window while keeping the host packet pair much
closer to normal USB timing.
---
 drivers/misc/fruitjam_usbhost.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/drivers/misc/fruitjam_usbhost.c b/drivers/misc/fruitjam_usbhost.c
--- a/drivers/misc/fruitjam_usbhost.c
+++ b/drivers/misc/fruitjam_usbhost.c
@@ -74,7 +74,7 @@
 #define FJ_USBHOST_SETUP_GAP_MAX_BYTES 16u
 #define FJ_USBHOST_SETUP_GAP_IDLE_FULL_BYTE 0xffu
 #define FJ_USBHOST_SETUP_GAP_IDLE_LOW_BYTE 0x55u
-#define FJ_USBHOST_HCD_ACK_ARM_GAP_BYTES 16u
+#define FJ_USBHOST_HCD_ACK_ARM_GAP_BYTES 4u
 #define FJ_USBHOST_FRAME_RETRY_DEFAULT 8u
 #define FJ_USBHOST_FRAME_RETRY_MAX 64u
 #define FJ_USBHOST_HANDSHAKE_PACKET_TIMEOUT_US 20u
